# TEST COVERAGE SKILL

## Goal
Add tests that cover explicitly defined existing behavior.

---

## Input
- A precise description of the behavior to cover

---

## Output
- One or more tests covering ONLY the specified behavior

---

## Rules

- Tests MUST follow Given / When / Then
- Tests MUST validate observable behavior only

- Tests MAY pass immediately (existing behavior)
- Tests MAY fail if behavior is incorrect

---

## STRICT CONSTRAINTS

❌ DO NOT introduce new behavior  
❌ DO NOT assume missing requirements  
❌ DO NOT extend scope beyond input  
❌ DO NOT modify production code  

---

## Scope Rule

- Cover EXACTLY what is described
- No additional scenarios

---

## Anti-Drift Rule

If behavior is unclear:
👉 DO NOT guess  
👉 DO NOT implement  
👉 Only test what is explicitly stated  